textBeforeTable: OSRAP Memorandums are frequently issued as a source of information concerning policy and procedures, system problems/solutions, and time deadlines. These memorandums inform and instruct state agencies of proper accounting policies and procedures relating to the recording and reporting of financial activity. These memorandums may appear differently depending on the browser you are using. Several memorandums have attachments which are not included here. If you have a problem viewing any of these documents or need an attachment for a memorandum, please call 225-342-1097.
